You need a slight modification on your service as,

     init() {
        return this.httpclient.post&lt;User&gt;(&#39;/loadData&#39;, {});
    }

In SomeService.ts: `.map(data =&gt; this.data);`  that can be omitted but that is the culprit. This effectively swaps the returned result `data` for the value of the field `data` set on the instance. If you really wanted to return what was passed in you should remove the keyword `this` which makes it `.map(data =&gt; data);`

--- 

    init() : Observable&lt;User&gt; {
      return this.httpclient.post&lt;User&gt;(&#39;/loadData&#39;, {});
    }

or if you want to alter the response

    init() : Observable&lt;User&gt; {
      return this.httpclient.post&lt;User&gt;(&#39;/loadData&#39;, {}).pipe(map(data =&gt; {
         // alter data here
         return data; // not this.data
       }));
    }

Finally you should specify return types on your methods so your code can benefit from type safety. I have added `Observable&lt;User&gt;` as the return type to the `init` method declaration.

